@node Overview
@chapter Overview

@samp{bibtex-extras.el} extends Emacs' built-in @samp{bibtex-mode} with functions
for manipulating Bib@TeX{} entries and fields, integrating with the @samp{ebib}
bibliography manager, and automating common tasks in a Bib@LaTeX{}
workflow.  It depends on @samp{ebib} for database operations and @samp{el-patch}
for patching built-in Bib@TeX{} functions.

The package provides a comprehensive set of getter and setter functions
for Bib@TeX{} fields, making it easy to read, write, and modify field
values programmatically.  These functions are used by other packages in
the extras ecosystem (such as @samp{ebib-extras.el} and @samp{eww-extras.el}) as
building blocks for higher-level operations.

For daily use, the package offers commands to open the current entry in
Ebib, move entries between bibliography files, convert misnamed fields
(e.g., Zotero's ``titleaddon'' to the standard ``journaltitle''), attach
downloaded files to entries, and escape special characters in Bib@TeX{}
files.

The package also includes a custom sorting predicate that replicates
Ebib's sorting behavior, ensuring consistent ordering regardless of
whether the buffer is sorted by @samp{bibtex-mode} or @samp{ebib}.

Two @samp{el-patch} modifications adjust built-in behavior: one adds
``urldate'' to the year lookup fields for automatic key generation, and
the other changes the page-dashes formatter to add a missing en-dash
rather than remove an existing one.

