@node Opening entries in Ebib
@section Opening entries in Ebib

@findex bibtex-extras-open-in-ebib
The command @code{bibtex-extras-open-in-ebib} opens the Bib@TeX{} entry at point
in the Ebib interface.  It saves the current buffer, reloads the
corresponding Ebib database to reflect any recent edits, switches to
the entry in Ebib, and displays the entry buffer.

This is useful when you are editing a Bib@TeX{} file directly and want to
switch to Ebib's richer interface for operations like viewing associated
files, editing fields with completion, or navigating cross-references.

@node Setting fields interactively
@section Setting fields interactively

@findex bibtex-extras-set-field
The command @code{bibtex-extras-set-field} prompts for a field name and a
value, then sets that field in the current entry.  If the field already
exists, it replaces the value; if it does not, it creates the field.
This command was adapted from @code{bibtex-set-field} in @samp{doi-utils.el}.

@node Attaching files from URLs
@section Attaching files from URLs

@findex bibtex-extras-url-to-pdf-attach
@findex bibtex-extras-url-to-html-attach
The command @code{bibtex-extras-url-to-pdf-attach} generates a PDF from the
URL field of the current Bib@TeX{} entry (using @code{eww-extras-url-to-file}
from @samp{eww-extras.el}) and attaches the resulting file to the entry.
This provides a one-step workflow for archiving web resources alongside
their bibliographic records.

The command @code{bibtex-extras-url-to-html-attach} performs the equivalent
operation for HTML files.  Both commands require the entry to have a
``url'' field.

@node Escaping special characters
@section Escaping special characters

@findex bibtex-extras-escape-special-characters
The command @code{bibtex-extras-escape-special-characters} scans the current
Bib@TeX{} file and escapes unescaped special characters (@samp{$}, @samp{%}, @samp{#},
@samp{&}) by prepending a backslash.  It skips the ``url'' and ``file'' fields,
where these characters are legitimate.

This is useful after importing entries from external sources that may
not properly escape @LaTeX{}-special characters.

