@node Getting entry and field data
@section Getting entry and field data

@findex bibtex-extras-get-key
@findex bibtex-extras-get-field
@findex bibtex-extras-get-field-name
@findex bibtex-extras-get-field-in-string
@findex bibtex-extras-get-entry-as-string
The function @code{bibtex-extras-get-key} returns the citation key of the
Bib@TeX{} entry at point (e.g., ``Author2024'').  It narrows to the entry
and extracts the key from the entry header.

The function @code{bibtex-extras-get-field} returns the value of a named
field in the current entry.  Whitespace (newlines, tabs, multiple
spaces) within the value is normalized to single spaces.  It returns
@code{nil} if the field is empty or absent.

The function @code{bibtex-extras-get-field-name} returns the name of the
Bib@TeX{} field at point.  This is useful for context-dependent operations.

The function @code{bibtex-extras-get-field-in-string} extracts a field value
from a Bib@TeX{} entry represented as a string.  It creates a temporary
buffer, inserts the string, and delegates to @code{bibtex-extras-get-field}.

The function @code{bibtex-extras-get-entry-as-string} returns the complete
Bib@TeX{} entry at point (or a specified KEY) as a string.  When an
optional FIELD argument is provided, it returns only that field's value.
The search can be restricted to specific FILES or defaults to
@code{bibtex-files}.

@node Setting and modifying fields
@section Setting and modifying fields

@findex bibtex-extras-add-or-update-field
@findex bibtex-extras-append-to-field
@findex bibtex-extras-kill-field
@findex bibtex-extras-convert-titleaddon-to-journaltitle
The function @code{bibtex-extras-add-or-update-field} creates a field with
the given value if it does not exist, or updates its value if it does.
It combines @code{bibtex-make-field} and @code{bibtex-set-field} into a single
operation.

The function @code{bibtex-extras-append-to-field} appends a value to an
existing field, using a configurable delimiter (defaulting to ``;'').  If
the field is empty, it sets the value directly.  This is useful for
fields like ``keywords'' that accumulate multiple values.

The function @code{bibtex-extras-kill-field} removes a named field from the
current entry entirely.

The function @code{bibtex-extras-convert-titleaddon-to-journaltitle} renames
the ``titleaddon'' field to ``journaltitle'' in the current entry.  This
corrects a common issue with entries imported via the Zotero translation
server, which records the online publication venue in ``titleaddon''
rather than the standard Bib@LaTeX{} ``journaltitle'' field.

@node Moving entries
@section Moving entries

@findex bibtex-extras-move-entry
The function @code{bibtex-extras-move-entry} moves a Bib@TeX{} entry identified
by KEY from its current bibliography file to a TARGET file.  It locates
the source file using @code{ebib-extras-get-file-of-key}, kills the entry
from the source buffer, and yanks it at the end of the target buffer,
saving both.  Ebib must be open for the source file lookup to work.

@node Attaching files to entries
@section Attaching files to entries

@findex bibtex-extras-url-to-file-attach
@findex bibtex-extras-attach-file-to-entry
The function @code{bibtex-extras-url-to-file-attach} generates a file of the
specified type from the entry's URL field and attaches it using a
callback.  It is the shared implementation behind
@code{bibtex-extras-url-to-pdf-attach} and @code{bibtex-extras-url-to-html-attach}
(@ref{Attaching files from URLs}).

The function @code{bibtex-extras-attach-file-to-entry} attaches a file to
the Bib@TeX{} entry whose key matches the file's base name.  It is used as
a callback by the URL-to-file download functions.

@node Sorting entries
@section Sorting entries

@findex bibtex-extras-entry-sorter
@findex bibtex-extras-lessp
The function @code{bibtex-extras-entry-sorter} returns a list containing the
entry key and a flag indicating whether the entry has a ``crossref''
field.  It is used by @code{bibtex-maintain-sorted-entries} as the key
extraction function.

The function @code{bibtex-extras-lessp} is the comparison predicate for
sorting Bib@TeX{} entries.  Entries with a ``crossref'' field are placed
before others and sorted in reverse alphabetical order by key.  All
remaining entries are sorted alphabetically.  This replicates Ebib's
sorting behavior, ensuring that sorting by either tool produces the same
result.

@node Miscellaneous helpers
@section Miscellaneous helpers

@findex bibtex-extras-replace-element-by-name
The function @code{bibtex-extras-replace-element-by-name} replaces an
element in a list whose @code{car} matches a target name with a new element.
It modifies the list in place.

